Economy of Mexico


Mexico City is the most important financial and economic center in Mexico



Currency
Mexican peso (MXN$)
1 US$ = 17.50 MXN (2017)



Fiscal year

Calendar



Trade organizations

APEC, NAFTA, OECD and WTO


Statistics


GDP

$1.5trillion (nominal; 2016)[1]
$2.5trillion (PPP; 2016))[2]


GDP rank
13th (nominal) / 11th (PPP)



GDP growth

2.6% (2015), 2.3% (2016e),
1.8% (2017f), 2.2% (2018f)[3]



GDP per capita


$8,700 (2016) (nominal)[4]
$18,900 (2016) (PPP)[4]



GDP by sector

agriculture: 3.6%, industry: 36.6%, services: 59.8% (2013 est.)[5]



Inflation (CPI)

 2.5% (2015 est.)



Population below poverty line

 13.8% (2015)[6][7]



Gini coefficient

 48.1 (2015) [8]



Labor force

53 million (2015 est.)



Labor force by occupation

agriculture: 13.4%, industry: 24.1%, services: 61.9% (2011)


Unemployment
 6.5% (2015)



